[PyPI pyversions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/icalreporting.svg?style=flat)](https://pypi.org/pypi/icalreporting/)\n[![GitHub stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/jgressier/icalreporting.svg?style=flat&logo=github&label=Stars&logoColor=white)](https://github.com/jgressier/icalreporting)\n[![PyPi downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/icalreporting.svg?style=flat)](https://pypistats.org/packages/icalreporting)\n[![codecov](https://img.shields.io/codecov/c/github/jgressier/icalreporting.svg?style=flat)](https://codecov.io/gh/jgressier/icalreporting)\n\n[![Codacy Badge](https://app.codacy.com/project/badge/Grade/d32cf67a5fa242c88bb1568277f1d60e)](https://app.codacy.com/gh/jgressier/icalreporting/dashboard?utm_source=gh&utm_medium=referral&utm_content=&utm_campaign=Badge_grade)[![Doc](https://readthedocs.org/projects/icalreporting/badge/?version=latest)](https://readthedocs.org/projects/icalreporting/)\n[![Slack](https://img.shields.io/static/v1?logo=slack&label=slack&message=contact&style=flat)](https://join.slack.com/t/isae-opendev/shared_invite/zt-obqywf6r-UUuHR4_hc5iTzyL5bFCwpw\n)\n\n### Features\n\n- able to load ical files and fill a pandas database\n- parse the pandas database to identify project and creates a worksheet tables\n- export to open document XLSX file\n\n### Installation\n\n```bash\npip install --upgrade icalreporting\n```\nThis automatic installation will get needed dependencies. \n\n### Requirements\n\nsee [requirements.txt](https://github.com/jgressier/icalreporting/blob/master/requirements.txt)\n\n### Usage\n\nWhen installed, you just need to put a set a ical files in a folder for a project. You will be able to create a reporting file with the following lines.\n\n```python\nfrom icalreporting.reporting import Project\nprj = Project(name=\"Big-Project\", folder=\"examples/projectA\", start=\"2023-01-01\", end=\"2024-01-01\")\nprj.load_ics()  # read files\nwb = prj.workbook()  # create workbook\nwb.save(\"projectA.xlsx\")  # save it to file\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "icalreporting.icaltools", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "engine", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile._read_icalendar", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile._read_ical", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile.read", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile.nevents", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile.filter_summary", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "keywords", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile.clean_events", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile.normalize_to_full_minutes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "delta", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Ensures a timedelta is represented in full minutes.\nRounds seconds to the nearest minute and returns a new timedelta."]}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile.normalize_vtimezone", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "icalreporting.icaltools.IcalFile._engines", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "icalreporting", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "icalreporting.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "icalreporting.reporting", "documentation": ["reporting module\n\nThis module uses an ical loader package to fill a pandas database which is parsed to generate a workbook and worksheets\n\nThe difficulty may be to handle recurrent events.\n\nnote..:\n    existing ical loading packages\n    - ixsts (local, non pip) from N. Garcia-Rosa\n    - icalendar\n    - icalevents (fork of icalendar)\n    - ics-py\n    - ical (handle recurring events)"], "functions": [{"name": "icalreporting.reporting.ical_to_dframe", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "startdate", "type": {"name": "datetime", "xref": {"fqname": "datetime.datetime", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "enddate", "type": {"name": "datetime", "xref": {"fqname": "datetime.datetime", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["read a file in ICAL format and create events between 2 dates\ncan handle recurrent events\n\nArgs:\n   